    "description": "\nLocalized heavy rainfall in slow-moving thunderstorms possible today.\n\nWhat:\nHighly localized heavy rainfall amounts of 40 to 60 mm.\n\nWhen:\nThis afternoon.\n\nAdditional information:\nIsolated thunderstorms are expected to affect areas west of Lake Superior again today. Due to the expected slow motion of these thunderstorms, some areas may receive significant amounts. The heaviest amounts should be highly localized with the vast majority of the region receiving little rainfall.\n\nFor information concerning flooding, please consult your local Conservation Authority or Ontario Ministry of Natural Resources office. Visit Ontario.ca/floods for the latest details.\n\n###\n\nPlease continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to ONstorm@ec.gc.ca or post reports on X using #ONStorm.\n",
